place.name: THEMELTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: THEMELTHORPE, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 5 miles ENE of Elmham r. station. Post town, Foulsham, under Thetford. Acres, 652. Real property., £1,085. Pop., 68. Houses, 18. The manor belongs to Lord Hastings. The living is a rectory, annexed to Bintree. The church is ancient. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
